23:00.117 --> 23:02.729
Hey, bud?

23:02.772 --> 23:04.339
There's your muffs.

23:08.212 --> 23:16.917
♪♪

23:16.960 --> 23:25.665
♪♪

23:25.708 --> 23:34.456
♪♪

23:34.500 --> 23:43.204
♪♪

23:43.247 --> 23:48.252
It's -- It's like
a trail of his stuff.

23:48.296 --> 23:49.602
[ Sighs ]

23:49.645 --> 23:52.039
It ends here.

23:52.082 --> 23:54.781
Why does he wear
that gear?

23:54.824 --> 23:57.653
Blow to the head.

23:57.697 --> 23:59.742
To his little head.

23:59.786 --> 24:02.310
♪♪

24:02.353 --> 24:06.488
He can't really face the world
head-on anymore.

24:06.532 --> 24:10.100
♪♪

24:10.144 --> 24:12.494
Glenn: Did you ever know that
you can go for a lot of days

24:12.538 --> 24:14.365
without eating food?

24:14.409 --> 24:18.718
But you can only live
like three days without water?

24:18.761 --> 24:20.937
My new friend Paul told me that

24:20.981 --> 24:23.505
'cause he was worried about me
getting lost out here,

24:23.549 --> 24:25.507
and he asked me how long
did I think you can go

24:25.551 --> 24:27.117
without drinking water,

24:27.161 --> 24:29.163
and I said, "A long time
'cause you can drink

24:29.206 --> 24:31.426
Pepsi and apple juice
and stuff,"

24:31.470 --> 24:33.384
and he said,
"That's not what I mean.

24:33.428 --> 24:34.864
What I mean is,
how long can you go

24:34.908 --> 24:36.213
without drinking anything?"

24:36.257 --> 24:37.693
And I said, "Oh."

24:37.737 --> 24:39.565
And he said, "Three days."

24:39.608 --> 24:42.089
So, good to know...

24:42.132 --> 24:44.439
'cause I'm lost,
and it's been a while

24:44.483 --> 24:47.964
since I've had apple juice
or Pepsi or anything.

24:48.008 --> 24:49.879
Until I met my friend Paul --

24:49.923 --> 24:52.752
We're in the early stages
of our friendship journey,

24:52.795 --> 24:55.363
and he teaches me things
along the way.

24:55.406 --> 24:58.366
Until I met Paul,
I didn't know how many things

24:58.409 --> 25:00.063
I didn't know about everything.

25:00.107 --> 25:02.065
He says my dad
didn't really raise me,

25:02.109 --> 25:05.547
and I'm sort of like a wolf boy
who was, like, raised

25:05.591 --> 25:07.941
by the wind or plants
or something

25:07.984 --> 25:10.073
and who doesn't know stuff.

25:10.117 --> 25:12.423
I guess he's right
about my dad.

25:12.467 --> 25:14.817
My dad spends
a lot of time in A.A.

25:16.950 --> 25:19.082
He still drinks.

25:19.126 --> 25:22.433
He just likes
the shrimp cocktails...

25:22.477 --> 25:24.697
at A.A.

25:24.740 --> 25:26.394
Then he likes
the regular cocktails

25:26.437 --> 25:29.919
at Toby's Six Guns
in Half Acre.

25:29.963 --> 25:33.270
They call him the town drunk.

25:33.314 --> 25:35.490
I don't know why.

25:35.534 --> 25:37.840
I mean, I know why --
'cause he's drunk all the time,

25:37.884 --> 25:41.452
but there are other guys
in Half Acre who are, too.

25:41.496 --> 25:44.630
So I don't know why
he'sthe town drunk,

25:44.673 --> 25:47.067
but he is.

25:47.110 --> 25:48.982
Anyway...

25:49.025 --> 25:52.551
it's Father's Day -- today.

25:52.594 --> 25:54.770
♪♪

25:54.814 --> 25:56.598
I bought my dad this sombrero,

25:56.642 --> 25:59.383
which I'm supposed to be
camping with the guys,

25:59.427 --> 26:01.385
so I don't know how
I'm gonna explain

26:01.429 --> 26:03.126
where I got him a sombrero,

26:03.170 --> 26:06.477
but I think I'm gonna die
out here anyway, so...

26:06.521 --> 26:08.349
♪♪

26:08.392 --> 26:10.220
What did I do wrong?

26:10.264 --> 26:12.745
Why am I lost?

26:12.788 --> 26:15.617
I don't always trust
my decision-makings

26:15.661 --> 26:19.186
due to my dad being...

26:19.229 --> 26:21.014
Well, there are some things

26:21.057 --> 26:23.146
that I've had
to learn on my own,

26:23.190 --> 26:25.758
and that's okay.

26:25.801 --> 26:29.326
Like, I learned that west
is always to the left.

26:29.370 --> 26:34.114
So after I bought the sombrero
in the sombrero gift store,

26:34.157 --> 26:36.333
I tried to get
on the right bus,

26:36.377 --> 26:38.814
and this guy told me
to go west.

26:38.858 --> 26:40.250
The bus to Hermosillo

26:40.294 --> 26:42.339
is on the west side
of the station.

26:42.383 --> 26:45.038
♪♪

26:45.081 --> 26:46.692
Thank you.

26:46.735 --> 26:51.914
♪♪

26:51.958 --> 26:57.137
♪♪

26:57.180 --> 27:01.315
I bumped into some rough teens
on my way left

27:01.358 --> 27:02.969
at the station.

27:03.012 --> 27:04.579
They started fucking with me.

27:04.623 --> 27:06.712
I think they wanted my shoes
or something --

27:06.755 --> 27:09.845
or my dad's sombrero,
which they didn't get.

27:09.889 --> 27:11.325
I fought them off.

27:11.368 --> 27:12.674
Ow.

27:12.718 --> 27:13.762
Ow!

27:13.806 --> 27:16.417
I started screaming from pain,

27:16.460 --> 27:18.506
but that spooked the dudes.

27:18.549 --> 27:21.901
So they only took my belt,
not my dad's sombrero

27:21.944 --> 27:23.946
or the $2,000 I'm supposed
to bring to the bank

27:23.990 --> 27:25.644
for my friend Paul,

27:25.687 --> 27:27.167
'cause that's in my underwear.

27:27.210 --> 27:30.649
So I still have it, but, man,

27:30.692 --> 27:34.000
I'm lost as shit,
just walking left,

27:34.043 --> 27:36.785
hoping to get back home because
I wrote a stupid Moon note,

27:36.829 --> 27:41.007
and soon, they're gonna think
I got kidnapped or something.

27:41.050 --> 27:49.189
♪♪

27:49.232 --> 27:57.371
♪♪

27:57.414 --> 28:05.596
♪♪

28:05.640 --> 28:13.735
♪♪

28:13.779 --> 28:21.917
♪♪

28:21.961 --> 28:23.919
[ Rod casts ]

28:23.963 --> 28:25.921
[ Water splashes ]

28:25.965 --> 28:27.706
[ Reel clicking ]

28:37.890 --> 28:39.805
[ Cap clatters ]

29:02.915 --> 29:06.745
[ Dialing ]

29:06.788 --> 29:08.790
[ Ringing]

29:08.834 --> 29:11.575
[ Telephone ringing ]

29:16.537 --> 29:18.365
Glenn: Hello.

29:18.408 --> 29:20.933
You've reached Pirdoo Pawn.
This is Glenn Pirdoo.

29:20.976 --> 29:23.457
I'm not here to provide
prompt assistance right now.

29:23.500 --> 29:25.764
Please leave your number,
and I will call you back --

29:25.807 --> 29:29.724
for assistance
and all your pawn needs.

29:29.768 --> 29:31.770
[ Beep]

29:43.477 --> 29:46.132
What's your plan, man?

29:46.175 --> 29:48.090
I'm thinkin'.

29:50.484 --> 29:53.313
It's Father's Day.

29:53.356 --> 29:55.794
What?

29:55.837 --> 29:57.230
Today.

29:59.885 --> 30:01.800
It's Father's Day.

30:07.066 --> 30:09.198
Remember how
I told you I...

30:09.242 --> 30:12.506
killed three people?

30:12.549 --> 30:16.075
Yeah.
I remember that.

30:16.118 --> 30:18.991
But I whispered it?

30:19.034 --> 30:21.341
Yeah.
I remember that, too.

30:21.384 --> 30:22.908
'Cause I didn't want
anyone to know?

30:22.951 --> 30:24.692
Yeah.

30:29.305 --> 30:33.005
Well, my dad knew...

30:33.048 --> 30:35.268
about all three.

30:38.097 --> 30:41.622
All about me.

30:41.665 --> 30:44.190
And he loved me anyway.

30:48.194 --> 30:51.893
He came to me one day,
and he said,

30:51.937 --> 30:55.288
"New Leaf,
I want you to know --"

30:55.331 --> 30:57.246
He called you New Leaf?

30:59.596 --> 31:01.250
Yes.

31:02.861 --> 31:06.603
It was important to me...

31:06.647 --> 31:09.171
to turn the page.

31:09.215 --> 31:11.565
And he respected that.

31:11.608 --> 31:15.177
And he came to me 'cause he knew
I contained secrets.

31:16.875 --> 31:20.052
And he said,
"New Leaf...

31:20.095 --> 31:22.619
tell me everything."

31:26.058 --> 31:28.930
And I did.

31:28.974 --> 31:32.760
And the first thing
he said was,

31:32.803 --> 31:34.936
"Son, I love you."

31:40.028 --> 31:42.161
What else did he say?

31:47.035 --> 31:49.646
I don't know.

31:49.690 --> 31:51.170
I never heard
another sound

31:51.213 --> 31:55.696
other than
the first thing he said...

31:55.739 --> 32:00.266
which remained ringing
and ringing in my head

32:00.309 --> 32:04.400
like a bell of love...

32:04.444 --> 32:07.490
forever.

32:07.534 --> 32:09.536
My dad.

32:23.376 --> 32:25.247
[ Door rattles ]

32:28.642 --> 32:30.426
[ Door rattles ]

32:40.436 --> 32:44.136
Hector: I'm not
gonna hurt you.

32:44.179 --> 32:46.877
I'm just saying, the only person
that's gotten hurt,

32:46.921 --> 32:49.315
your husband hurt him,
so...

32:49.358 --> 32:53.014
And an ice-cream man,

32:53.058 --> 32:55.669
but that was extenuating.

32:55.712 --> 32:57.279
Yeah.

32:57.323 --> 32:59.803
Ma: My son's nowhere
near here --

32:59.847 --> 33:01.980
my son.

33:02.023 --> 33:04.721
We were told
he was here.

33:04.765 --> 33:08.029
He's nowhere
near here, you.

33:08.073 --> 33:09.813
I know.

33:09.857 --> 33:12.642
I understand
your plan --

33:12.686 --> 33:15.471
parts of your plan.

33:15.515 --> 33:17.038
Part of this
awful thing,

33:17.082 --> 33:20.607
I believed my son
was terribly ill.

33:20.650 --> 33:22.783
You're gonna be okay.

33:22.826 --> 33:24.741
Where's my husband?

33:24.785 --> 33:26.265
He's okay, too.

33:26.308 --> 33:28.136
I mean...

33:28.180 --> 33:31.444
I have his thumb,
but, yeah.

33:31.487 --> 33:33.794
Good Lord.

33:33.837 --> 33:36.275
You want it?

33:36.318 --> 33:38.973
What are you
talking about, you?

33:39.017 --> 33:42.063
I didn't do it.
He did it.

33:42.107 --> 33:44.196
I just have it.

33:44.239 --> 33:48.026
God damn it.

33:48.069 --> 33:50.593
[ Sighs ]

33:54.423 --> 33:56.904
I hurt a girl.

33:56.947 --> 33:59.602
What?

33:59.646 --> 34:02.388
I hurt a girl, you.

34:05.043 --> 34:07.088
I probably hurt her
very badly.

34:07.132 --> 34:09.786
I probably hurt her
forever.

34:09.830 --> 34:13.355
Yeah, well, that's, like --
that's, like, fucked up, so...

34:13.399 --> 34:15.227
Don't you swear at me.

34:15.270 --> 34:16.880
I'm not swearing
at you, man.

34:16.924 --> 34:19.492
I'm just swearing 'cause --
'cause everything's messed up.

34:19.535 --> 34:22.843
I'm out of shape.
It's Father's Day.

34:22.886 --> 34:24.453
Fuck,
I should be at the school

34:24.497 --> 34:29.067
talking about how cool my job is
compared to the car guys.

34:32.157 --> 34:33.375
You have children?

34:33.419 --> 34:35.247
Yeah, I do.

34:35.290 --> 34:36.639
Sort of.

34:36.683 --> 34:38.685
How can you sort of
have children?

34:38.728 --> 34:41.992
No, I-I -- I totally
have them, yeah.

34:42.036 --> 34:44.995
I just --
I just don't have --

34:45.039 --> 34:46.432
I don't know.
They don't --

34:46.475 --> 34:50.088
They don't listen to me
or, like, look at me.

34:52.786 --> 34:57.225
Kids obey inner laws
at certain ages.

34:57.269 --> 34:58.966
Yeah, well --

34:59.009 --> 35:00.402
Yeah, well, when I --

35:00.446 --> 35:02.317
when I try to talk to them
about things,

35:02.361 --> 35:04.319
about life,
they don't listen,

35:04.363 --> 35:06.930
and then when I think of --
I think of something

35:06.974 --> 35:09.063
that they'll like
and admire,

35:09.107 --> 35:11.674
they --
they don't see them.

35:11.718 --> 35:13.328
They don't.

35:15.461 --> 35:16.810
I'm fucked.

35:16.853 --> 35:17.941
Why?

35:17.985 --> 35:19.204
Bank.

35:19.247 --> 35:20.944
Bank.

35:20.988 --> 35:25.079
I had to -- had to get
some money in the bank.

35:25.123 --> 35:27.777
My wife, she just buys,
and --

35:27.821 --> 35:29.344
Never mind.
Never mind.

35:29.388 --> 35:32.521
What?

35:32.565 --> 35:35.307
She buys great gifts
for the kids and me --

35:35.350 --> 35:38.745
birthday, Father's Day
every year.

35:38.788 --> 35:40.616
Fuck, yeah.

35:40.660 --> 35:44.272
I'm like, "Whoa. What?
How did you know?"

35:44.316 --> 35:47.275
I mean, totally, I'm like,
"How did you know?"

35:47.319 --> 35:48.929
And then she --

35:48.972 --> 35:50.496
she actually thinks
of these things.

35:50.539 --> 35:52.672
You know, not --
not like the morning of,

35:52.715 --> 35:55.153
when I'm like, "Shit.

35:55.196 --> 35:58.504
It was just her birthday.
Now it's her birthday again?"

35:58.547 --> 36:02.508
So, like, I have
to go out and --

36:02.551 --> 36:04.597
and get something
right away

36:04.640 --> 36:07.077
that looks like it was
previously planned.

36:07.121 --> 36:09.732
You know, Marisol --
she doesn't do that.

36:09.776 --> 36:11.734
She gets it right.
She's the best.

36:11.778 --> 36:15.173
You know, so what
I'm saying is, today,

36:15.216 --> 36:17.479
when she go picks up my thing
for Father's Day,

36:17.523 --> 36:20.003
it's probably gonna
be a little --

36:20.047 --> 36:24.791
a little expensive and cool,
and then --

36:24.834 --> 36:27.185
and then she's gonna look
at our bank balance

36:27.228 --> 36:30.666
and see that it's less
than she thinks because I...

36:30.710 --> 36:36.977
I actually previously
planned and bought

36:37.020 --> 36:41.111
a very thoughtful gift...
for another woman.

36:41.155 --> 36:43.026
Yeah.

36:43.070 --> 36:46.421
What are you making
a hole for, you?

36:46.465 --> 36:48.684
Uh, you.

36:48.728 --> 36:50.947
But not to --

36:50.991 --> 36:54.124
Listen, I'm gonna put
a breathing mechanism in there.

36:54.168 --> 36:55.561
Don't worry.

36:55.604 --> 36:57.519
I got a plan.

36:57.563 --> 36:59.304
Oh, yeah.

36:59.347 --> 37:02.568
Oh.

37:02.611 --> 37:04.134
[ Grunts ]

37:10.793 --> 37:13.970
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

37:56.361 --> 38:00.321
You shouldn't have come, man,
to Mexico.

38:00.365 --> 38:03.063
Could
fuck everything up.

38:03.106 --> 38:06.153
Well, I have to
be here, James --

38:06.196 --> 38:07.459
so-called James.

38:07.502 --> 38:10.810
It's not so-called.
It's...

38:10.853 --> 38:12.202
It's James.

38:12.246 --> 38:15.162
I have to be here
'cause you're here,

38:15.205 --> 38:17.251
and if this Chili's device
goes off,

38:17.295 --> 38:20.080
if I hear
that awful buzz

38:20.123 --> 38:23.605
before this money's
tucked back in the bank,

38:23.649 --> 38:27.566
I'm gonna
fuckin' kill you.

38:27.609 --> 38:29.045
Okay.

38:29.089 --> 38:32.788
So, hence, I need to be
where you are --

38:32.832 --> 38:35.008
to kill you...

38:35.051 --> 38:37.358
so-called James.

38:37.402 --> 38:40.187
[ Sighs ]

38:40.230 --> 38:41.667
Got it.

38:41.710 --> 38:44.104
Felipe
stopped the issuance,

38:44.147 --> 38:46.367
and I got a plan
to get Paul.

38:46.411 --> 38:48.500
Make sure that fucking
money gets in that
bank in Hermosillo.

38:48.543 --> 38:49.849
Okay.

38:55.333 --> 38:58.945
[ Bus engine idles ]

38:58.988 --> 39:02.862
You're going to Hermosillo
to find your little buddy?

39:02.905 --> 39:04.559
Then so am I.

39:08.389 --> 39:13.612
♪♪

39:13.655 --> 39:16.092
Glenn:
If they tell my story,

39:16.136 --> 39:18.834
they'll probably stop at
some point around here and go,

39:18.878 --> 39:20.749
"Hey, man.

39:20.793 --> 39:24.318
Why didn't you put the sombrero
on for element protection?"

39:24.362 --> 39:28.627
And I'll go,
"Because it's a gift,

39:28.670 --> 39:31.281
and I wanted my dad to have
a fresh sombrero

39:31.325 --> 39:32.500
if I make it home."

39:32.544 --> 39:36.809
♪♪

39:36.852 --> 39:39.028
My dad wasn't always a bad dad.

39:39.072 --> 39:40.900
Before he really started
drinking,

39:40.943 --> 39:42.684
he would read to me
and put me to sleep

39:42.728 --> 39:44.904
with "Call of the Wild."

39:44.947 --> 39:47.950
But he doesn't read it to me
anymore.

39:47.994 --> 39:50.562
But I still want to go home.

39:50.605 --> 39:53.042
♪♪

39:53.086 --> 39:54.566
My plan?

39:54.609 --> 39:57.133
To continue left
to the Pacific Ocean

39:57.177 --> 39:59.919
and to drink from it
and survive.

39:59.962 --> 40:09.407
♪♪

40:09.450 --> 40:18.851
♪♪

40:18.894 --> 40:28.338
♪♪

40:28.382 --> 40:37.783
♪♪

40:37.826 --> 40:47.227
♪♪

40:47.270 --> 40:56.671
♪♪

40:56.715 --> 41:06.159
♪♪

41:06.202 --> 41:15.603
♪♪

41:15.647 --> 41:25.091
♪♪

41:25.134 --> 41:27.528
James: Do you --
Do you still have the money?

41:27.572 --> 41:29.748
Glenn: Yeah --
in my underwear.

41:29.791 --> 41:31.532
W-Where are you?

41:31.576 --> 41:35.841
I finally found a phone, Paul,
but it might be a mirage.

41:35.884 --> 41:37.538
Well,
y-you're talking to me, right?

41:37.582 --> 41:39.061
Right.

41:39.105 --> 41:41.411
Yeah. So...
it's probably not a mirage.

41:41.455 --> 41:42.456
Right.

41:42.500 --> 41:44.763
So, okay.

41:44.806 --> 41:46.329
Where are you?

41:46.373 --> 41:47.766
I'm on a highway

41:47.809 --> 41:51.770
at the exit
for Hermosillo

41:51.813 --> 41:55.382
1-1-slash-2 kilometers...

41:55.425 --> 41:56.862
I think.

41:56.905 --> 41:58.385
I can hardly see.

41:58.428 --> 42:00.039
There's something wrong
with my vision now.

42:00.082 --> 42:01.649
Okay, okay.

42:01.693 --> 42:04.391
You're only a mile from here,
from the bank.

42:04.434 --> 42:06.872
I don't feel right, Paul.

42:06.915 --> 42:12.094
Even the darkness hurts now,
and the silence.

42:12.138 --> 42:14.009
W-W-We'll get some rest
in a bit.

42:14.053 --> 42:16.751
Just -- Just take the exit
and -- and keep heading west,

42:16.795 --> 42:18.013
and I'll meet you
at the bank.

42:18.057 --> 42:19.493
West?

42:19.537 --> 42:23.758
Yeah, toward the sun,
the setting sun.

42:23.802 --> 42:26.239
Towards the sun?

42:26.282 --> 42:27.283
Yeah.

42:27.327 --> 42:29.764
Into the sun?
Yeah.

42:29.808 --> 42:30.939
That's west?

42:30.983 --> 42:31.940
Yeah.

42:31.984 --> 42:33.986
Fuck.

42:34.029 --> 42:35.944
Sure?
What?

42:35.988 --> 42:37.598
Are you sure?

42:37.642 --> 42:39.121
About the sun
setting in the west?

42:39.165 --> 42:40.470
Yeah, yeah.

42:40.514 --> 42:41.994
Okay.

42:42.037 --> 42:43.561
Fuck.

42:43.604 --> 42:44.953
It's gonna hurt.

42:44.997 --> 42:46.433
You can do it, Glenn.

42:46.476 --> 42:48.827
Do you know what
the extra mile is?

42:48.870 --> 42:50.350
No.

42:50.393 --> 42:52.570
It's the last push you do
to do something important

42:52.613 --> 42:55.747
and friendly
in terms of friendship.

42:55.790 --> 42:57.313
Okay.

42:57.357 --> 43:01.013
Are youmy friend, Paul?

43:01.056 --> 43:03.276
Yes.

43:03.319 --> 43:05.365
And just wait till
we have the shared experience

43:05.408 --> 43:08.498
of you going into the sun
and more noise, probably,

43:08.542 --> 43:12.024
with the money
over the extra mile.

43:12.067 --> 43:14.461
We're gonna be real tight.

43:14.504 --> 43:17.203
Go the extra mile,
Glenn.

43:17.246 --> 43:18.508
Okay.

43:18.552 --> 43:21.990
Try to get a ride.

43:22.034 --> 43:23.688
Okay.

43:26.429 --> 43:27.692
Hey.

43:27.735 --> 43:28.997
Yeah?

43:29.041 --> 43:31.913
You feel alone
sometimes?

43:31.957 --> 43:34.263
Just when I'm alone...

43:34.307 --> 43:36.614
and when I'm with
other people.

43:36.657 --> 43:37.658
Yeah.

43:37.702 --> 43:39.965
Yeah.

43:40.008 --> 43:42.315
Hey, I'm in a gang.

43:43.098 --> 43:44.491
Cool.

43:44.534 --> 43:46.754
Yeah, we're cool.

43:46.798 --> 43:48.756
And you can join
my cool gang

43:48.800 --> 43:50.236
if you get here
with the money.

43:50.279 --> 43:53.848
You can be one of us
and -- and belong.

43:53.892 --> 43:57.069
I can be one of you
and belong?

43:57.112 --> 43:59.767
Totally. Totally.

43:59.811 --> 44:02.770
That's pretty
fucking cool.

44:02.814 --> 44:06.513
What are you called?

44:06.556 --> 44:08.080
The Special Boys.

44:08.123 --> 44:10.604
Cool.

44:10.648 --> 44:14.564
All right.
Get here.

44:14.608 --> 44:16.305
Hot damn.

44:16.349 --> 44:18.046
I want to be
a Special Boy.

44:18.090 --> 44:20.092
But y-you can't be one
till you get here.

44:21.746 --> 44:24.923
I don't have to
kill anyone, do I?

44:24.966 --> 44:26.402
No way.
We just --

44:26.446 --> 44:31.669
We just are filled
with togetherness and love.

44:31.712 --> 44:33.583
What do you do?

44:33.627 --> 44:38.980
Just, like...
feel those feelings together

44:39.024 --> 44:41.504
through events and stuff.

44:41.548 --> 44:43.463
[ Sighs ]

44:46.640 --> 44:48.686
Special Boy.

44:48.729 --> 44:51.036
[ Motorcycle approaching ]

45:06.834 --> 45:09.184
[ Engine revs ]

45:11.621 --> 45:13.885
Are you going
to the bank town?

45:13.928 --> 45:15.451
To where?

45:15.495 --> 45:18.411
To the town that's an extra mile
away from here?

45:18.454 --> 45:19.934
It has a bank in it.

45:19.978 --> 45:22.284
Yes -- Hermosillo?

45:22.328 --> 45:24.678
Can I have a ride,
please?

45:24.722 --> 45:28.203
Would your parents let you ride
without a helmet?

45:28.247 --> 45:29.857
My dad would, yeah.

45:29.901 --> 45:31.598
Cool.

